abstract: The establishment doesn’t have the credibility to stop the surging Sanders movement.
snippet: The establishment doesn’t have the credibility to stop the surging Sanders movement.
lead_paragraph: A half-hour before a Bernie Sanders rally on Saturday night in Iowa, a line snaked around the nearly 900-seat Ames City Auditorium, but no one else was being let in: The theater was full.

abstract: The former national security adviser shared his unease with the attorney general, who cited his own worries about the president’s conversations with the leaders of Turkey and China.
snippet: The former national security adviser shared his unease with the attorney general, who cited his own worries about the president’s conversations with the leaders of Turkey and China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — John R. Bolton, the former national security adviser, privately told Attorney General William P. Barr last year that he had concerns that President Trump was effectively granting personal favors to the autocratic leaders of Turkey and China, according to an unpublished manuscript by Mr. Bolton.

abstract: Diplomatic correspondents said the move appeared to retaliate against NPR for an interview that pressed Mr. Pompeo on his role in the Trump administration’s shadow foreign policy in Ukraine.
snippet: Diplomatic correspondents said the move appeared to retaliate against NPR for an interview that pressed Mr. Pompeo on his role in the Trump administration’s shadow foreign policy in Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The State Department will not allow NPR’s diplomatic correspondent on Secretary of State Mike Pompeo’s government airplane for an upcoming trip, which includes a stop in Ukraine, following the secretary’s extraordinary outburst last week over being questioned about Ukraine during an interview with the network.

headline_main: State Dept. Will Not Allow NPR Reporter on Pompeo’s Plane Following Interview
headline_print_headline: State Dept. Won’t Let NPR Reporter on Trip

abstract: In an unusual diplomatic moment, President Trump met with both Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel and his challenger, Benny Gantz, on the eve of releasing a Middle East peace plan.
snippet: In an unusual diplomatic moment, President Trump met with both Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel and his challenger, Benny Gantz, on the eve of releasing a Middle East peace plan.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For Benny Gantz, the leader of the centrist Blue and White Party in Israel, traveling to Washington on Monday to meet with President Trump at the same time as the man he is trying to defeat wasn’t exactly a state visit.

abstract: Iowa caucusgoers aren’t just asking about the one issue that’s dominating the headlines.
snippet: Iowa caucusgoers aren’t just asking about the one issue that’s dominating the headlines.
lead_paragraph: MARSHALLTOWN, Iowa — With three jurors in the impeachment trial traipsing about Iowa this past weekend, you’d expect someone — anyone! — planning to attend the Iowa caucuses to ask the presidential candidates about impeachment.

abstract: Ken Starr — yes, Ken Starr — wonders how America has arrived at the “age of impeachment.”
snippet: Ken Starr — yes, Ken Starr — wonders how America has arrived at the “age of impeachment.”
lead_paragraph: You have to hand it to the legal team defending President Trump in the Senate’s impeachment trial: It sticks to its story, even when confronted by new evidence pretty much demolishing that story.

abstract: John Bolton’s new memoir is titled “The Room Where It Happened,” nearly the same as a song from Lin-Manuel Miranda’s Broadway hit.
snippet: John Bolton’s new memoir is titled “The Room Where It Happened,” nearly the same as a song from Lin-Manuel Miranda’s Broadway hit.
lead_paragraph: Wait a minute. A lyric from a Broadway show is part of the most heated political discourse of the moment? Something from a musical has actually been appended to a major national talking point?
